Class Fair

  • java.lang.Object
    • package1.Event
      • package3.Fair

  • public class Fair
extends Event
    Class Fair is a subclass of Event, which allows the creation of Fair objects, including 3 inherited attributes and 2 new attributes. The 2 new attributes are made private for Part 2, allowing only the Fair class to access them directly.

      • equals

        public boolean equals​(java.lang.Object obj)
        equals method overrides method from Event class and checks to see if a passed object has the same attributes as an object of Fair class. If the passed object is null or not of the Fair class, then the method will return false. In Part 1, we can directly access the objects of the parent class and can return using this.attribute. In part 2, due to restriction of access rights, we must use the getter method of parent class in return statement using syntax this.getAttribute();
        Overrides:
        equals in class Event
        Returns:
        true when the passed object is of the Fair class and has the same value for every attribute
